b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe48343.htm)  [Next](sbe48345.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n27\\. From the yoni the body.\n\nOnly after having reached a yoni the soul, affected with a remnant of its\nworks, obtains a new body, and only in a body there can be the enjoyment of\npleasure and pain. When, therefore, previous to that the soul is said to reach\nether, wind, and so on, this can only mean that it enters into conjunction\nwith them.--Here terminates the adhikara _n_ a of 'that animated by another\nsoul.'\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: Second Pada: 1. In the intermediate sphere the creation is effected by\nthe soul](sbe48345.htm)\n\n"